records.addlTxt:
Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

AS TO COUNT 1:  The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  

AS TO COUNT 2:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on state's motion, the Court orders Count 2 DISMISSED AND READ-IN for the purpose of sentencing in Count 1.

Statements made as to Sentencing by the state, defense, and defendant.

COUNT 1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 2 YEARS with credit for 0 credit, Concurrent to time being served. 

The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 1 YEAR.  
The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 1 YEAR.


The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.  


CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*Obtain AODA assessment and complete recommended follow-up care/treatment;
*Absolute sobriety with random urine screens- no alcohol or illegal substances;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school or combination of both totaling 40 hours per week;
*No driving without valid license;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs by the end of supervision period;

The Court ordered all financial obligations to be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.

Defendant informed he may not possess and/or own any firearms.
Defendant informed he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been reinstated.  
Defendant informed of his right to appeal this sentence. 
Filed;
-Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement;
-Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
-Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
-Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence-copy to defendant.
